Let $A_1, A_2, A_3$ be $2 times 2$ matrices with entries in $CC$ (the
complex numbers). Let $"tr"$ denote the trace of a matrix (so $"tr"
mat(a, b; c, d) = a + d$). Suppose ${ A_1, A_2, A_3 }$ is closed under matrix
multiplication (i.e., given $i, j$, there exists $k$ such that $A_i A_j =
A_k$), and $"tr" (A_1 + A_2 + A_3) eq.not 3$.  Prove that there exists $i$ such
that $A_i A_j = A_j A_i$ for all $j$ (here $i, j$ are 1, 2 or 3).
